                    "description": "**IB Chinese A: Language & Literature** is a **Group 1** subject in the **International Baccalaureate Diploma Programme (IBDP)**. It explores **both literary and non-literary texts in Chinese, analyzing language use, meaning, and cultural contexts across various text types and themes**, with a strong focus on **textual analysis, comparative essay writing, and developing critical thinking and communication skills through oral and written assessments**.\n\nThe course is available at **Standard Level (SL, 150 teaching hours)** and **Higher Level (HL, 240 teaching hours)**, with **first assessment in 2024**.\n\n### Assessment at a Glance\n\n| **Assessment** | **Format** | **SL** | **HL** | **Weighting** |\n|---|---|---|---|---|\n| **Paper 1** | Guided analysis of unseen non-literary texts | 1 hr 15 min | 1 hr 30 min | 35% |\n| **Paper 2** | Comparative essay on studied literary works | 1 hr 45 min | 2 hrs | 35% |\n| **Individual Oral** | Oral commentary and discussion on text extracts | ~15 min | ~15 min | 30% |",
